text.tspan: Significant earthquakes per year, World, 2,150 BCE to 2017
Due to changes in data collection and reporting, recent data will be more complete than historical records.
Therefore, an increase in reported earthquakes over time doesn't necessarily indicate an actual increase.
Data source: National Geophysical Data Center (NGDC) of the NOAA
Note: A significant earthquake meets at least one of the following: caused deaths, moderate damage ($1 million or more), a magnitude
7.5 or greater, Modified Mercalli Intensity (MMI) X or greater, or generated a tsunami.
